deck:
He started to work for Lug (publishers) in the 1970s, mainly for touch-ups and covers. He worked in particular, from 1977 to 1980, in Blek the Rock produced by the Italian studio Essegesse. 

In 1980, he began out his first personal work, Photonik. Later, he created Fuzz and Fizzbi for Glénat, and, for Delcourt, drew part of the Aquablue series, written by Thierry Cailleteau.
